author: sussman
msg: Make our username/password prompting auth providers display the
authentication realm.
* auth.c (get_creds): take realmstring argument, and display when
prompting user.
(simple_prompt_first_creds, simple_prompt_next_creds,
username_prompt_first_creds, username_prompt_next_creds): update callers.
(prompt_iter_baton_t):  remember the original realmstring.

author: bdenny
msg: Some followup fixes to r5521/Issue #1108 ('svn log' for switched file reports
for unswitched file).
Specifically, fixes two holes in the logic, gets rid of compiler warnings,
and fleshes out the test cases.
* path.c
(svn_path_get_longest_ancestor): Make sure that we return NULL
if the protocol names are of different lengths, or if given one
path and one URL, regardless of the order of the targets.
Remove unused variables.
* target-test.py
(tests): Check that all paths and URLs get condensed, and that URLs
with protocol names of different lengths are handled correctly.

author: ballbach
msg: Updated the readme to indicate that I'm not going to keep the mandrake
9.0 spec file up to date any longer. It is becoming excruciatingly
difficult to do so as subversion requires newer versions of other
components.
* README: modified to reflect derelict status
